SIMPLE: headpiece
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Headpiece
<hw>Head"piece`</hw> <pr>(-p⟦emac⟧s`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Head.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In his <qex>headpiece</qex> he felt a sore pain.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A cap of defense; especially, an open one, as
distinguished from the closed helmet of the Middle Ages.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Understanding; mental faculty.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Eumenes had the best <qex>headpiece</qex> of all Alexander's
captains.</q> <rj><qau>Prideaux.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>An engraved ornament at the head of a chapter, or of
a page.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>headpin</ent>⟦br⟧
